--
-- Phase B (Task 4). The bath_body import gate is already open and the importers
-- redeployed; this migration reclassifies the EXISTING rows that predate the
-- gate. Target rows were produced by a dry-run of inferCategorisationForImport()
-- (the same function the importers use) over every active, non-merged product,
-- filtered to those CURRENTLY stored as top_category='skincare' that the detector
-- now routes to bath_body. 4,084 rows: body 3,439 / hand 645.
--
-- Safety:
--   * every UPDATE is guarded by `top_category = 'skincare'`, so a row that has
--     since changed category is skipped rather than clobbered;
--   * ids are explicit (no name-pattern predicate), so exactly the detector-matched
--     set is touched and nothing else — no makeup, hair, fragrance, face/active
--     skincare, or excluded gift_set/baby/intimate_health rows;
--   * subcategory/product_type/tags mirror the detector contract
--     (tags = ['bath_body', subcategory]), matching how the live fragrance rows
--     and future bath_body imports are stored.
--
-- Idempotent: re-running is a no-op (rows are no longer 'skincare' after the
-- first apply). Wrapped in a transaction.

begin;

